Review.Door: Marty, that was very interesting music. There's that word again, heavy. Why are things so heavy in the future. Is there a problem with the Earth's gravitational pull? No wait, Doc, the bruise, the bruise on your head, I know how that happened, you told me the whole story. you were standing on your toilet and you were hanging a clock, and you fell, and you hit your head on the sink, and that's when you came up with the idea for the flux capacitor, which makes time travel possible. So tell me, future boy, who's president of the United States in 1985? Hey Dad, George, hey, you on the bike.
